Malmaison, the country home of Napoleon and Josephine and also my favorite historical home. I love every little detail of decor and could move right in .. my pictures could never do it justice. If you have never been you must go next time in Paris. It’s a quick jaunt outside the city done in an afternoon. Much of my design inspiration relates back here in little ways… Thank you Chuck and Dino for the narrated tour from an authentic Frenchman! ❤️ #malmaison #napolean #napoleanandjosephine #directoire #French #Francophile #marymcdonaldstyle #decorationinterieur

Welcome to my Shell Grotto inspired  @kbshowhouse bedroom 2023! This designers were given the opportunity to reimagine rooms on the 5 floors of the glorious Beaux Arts River Mansion overlooking riverside drive lush parks.  My bedroom was designed around my new “Shell Grotto” wallpaper for @schumacher1889 coming this Summer, @schumacher1889 Portail Francais  high perfomance fabric and brand new @pattersonflynn1943 “compass” abaca rug. Anyone that knows me knows I love a collected room and any type of Coquillage! My contemporary plaster fixture by @lizobriengallery freshly reflected the shell theme. My glamorous and glorious canopy bed was made by the expert team  from @fineartsfurniture. My custom monogrammed linens by @peacockalley and beautiful window treatments by @theshadestore .. Our luscious paint by @benjaminmoore Thank goodness for MMInc team member @aija.marie.studio ! We got this installed .Could not have done it without you ! A special thanks to Nazira @nhandalp for keeping us all on track! Design tip: Two bold patterns can live side-by-side when separated by a neutral layer. For the windows of @kbshowhouse, designer @marymcdonaldinc turned to @TheShadeStore to craft three layers of custom window treatments. The base layer of a Woven Wood Shade reflects the natural elements of the room design, a Relaxed Roman Shade in a @Schumacher1889 fabric of her own design pulls in tones of blue from the dramatic Shell Grotto wallpaper for which the room is names and the simple cream Tailored Pleat drapery panels provide a visual break between the two different patterns. 

Achieve the look: 

Product: Waterfall Woven Wood Shades
Fabric: Sienna
Color: Almond

Product: Relaxed Roman Shades
Fabric: C.O.M by @Schumacher1889 

Product: Tailored Pleat Drapery
Fabric: C.O.M. by @Schumacher1889

McDonald, an award-winning, bicoastal designer and long-time Schumacher collaborator, waxes poetic about how different elements of a room contribute to the overall flair and dazzles us with her sharp wit and fierce decorating chops!

Mary McDonald has done it again! The award-winning interior designer and frequent Schumacher collaborator never fails to delight us with her stylish and original take on familiar classical forms. Take a behind the scenes look as the Schumacher team photographs Mary’s newest collection at her Hudson Valley home.

Her latest collection of fabrics, trims and wallcoverings is derived from a wide range of sources—from backgammon boards and Chinese porcelain to Portuguese tilework and Swedish architecture—and offers endless ways to create beautifully detailed interiors that are as livable as they are chic.

Head to the link in bio to see the full collection!

Thank you @verandamag and @steelemarcoux for including this magnificent property in your January 2024 historic preservation issue. Casa Della Porta in Palm Beach was considered Maurice Fatio’s best work and it’s hard not to agree. Thank you to my amazing clients for the opportunity to work on this magnificent beauty as well as @daniel.kahan.architect of @smithandmoorearchitects for his unerring direction. @benitzbuildingllc for all bathroom and bedroom renovation. Article @francesschultz Photos @brantleyphoto Thanks to my right hand at the time @studiokenna for seeing this great project through #verandamag #historicpreservation #palmbeachhistory #palmbeach #mauricefatio #casadellaporta #neutralpalette #historicdetails #marymcdonaldstyle

I can only hope Maurice Fatio would approve of our “Casa Della Porta” principal bath redesign which had been remodeled a couple of times already so we were not disturbing any 1920’s pristine stone or tile work thank goodness. I loved designing this arabescato marble paneled bath with custom nickel and oak vanities and shower with bolt details. We hoped to achieve a brand new 1920’s bath to seamlessly dovetail with the existing house. One of my favorites thanks to my amazing clients who supported my vision and @daniel.kahan.architect in tandem support executed by @benitzbuildingllc #casadellaporta #mauricefatio #mauricefatioarchitecture #PalmBeach #palmbeachhistoricalsociety #jeankarajiancollection #catchpoleandrye #bathroomdesign #arabescato #marymcdonaldstyle
